    <link>http://linn-guo.github.io/2025/zeno3/</link>
    <pubDate>Fri, 26 Sep 2025 13:37:25 &#43;0800</pubDate><author>
        <name>Lynn G</name>
    </author><guid>http://linn-guo.github.io/2025/zeno3/</guid>
    <description><![CDATA[<div class="featured-image">
                <img src="/img/zeno3_1.png" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">
            </div><h2 id="story-time-twist" class="headerLink">
    <a href="#story-time-twist" class="header-mark"></a>1 Story Time Twist</h2><p>The other night, I was reading The Tortoise and the Hare with my kid.
You know the ending — the rabbit takes a nap, the tortoise keeps going, and… yep, the tortoise wins. Classic.</p>
<p>But when we finished the story — yeah, you caught me — I just couldn&rsquo;t resist adding a twist: &quot; What if the very next day… they race again?&quot;</p>]]></description>
</item><item>
    <title>Zhuangzi&#39;s Stick</title>
    <link>http://linn-guo.github.io/2025/zeno2/</link>
    <pubDate>Thu, 25 Sep 2025 14:03:57 &#43;0800</pubDate><author>
        <name>Lynn G</name>
    </author><guid>http://linn-guo.github.io/2025/zeno2/</guid>
    <description><![CDATA[<div class="featured-image">
                <img src="/img/zhuangzi.png" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">
            </div><h2 id="story-time-twist" class="headerLink">
    <a href="#story-time-twist" class="header-mark"></a>1 Story Time Twist:</h2><p>Hey friends, remember our last treasure hunting story?</p>
<p>Leo had to move in infinite steps within a limited time, but since he was walking at a steady speed, he eventually reached the treasure. Cool, right?</p>
<p>But… what if we change the rules a little bit, like the daily speed is decreasing?</p>]]></description>
</item><item>
